  "text": "where |φ n are the corresponding eigenstates (here, for simplicity, we are assuming that the spectrum is discrete and non-degenerate; the formulae can be easily modified for more general cases). As emphasized in for example section 2 of [CITATION_1] , the heat kernel contains information about both zero and non-zero modes. Let us denote by n 0 A the number of zero modes of the operator A. Then, one has the following equation",
